==''Ally'' the sitcom==
In 1999, at the height of the show's popularity, a half-hour version entitled ''Ally''&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0210403/ &quot;Ally&quot; (1999) at IMDB]&lt;/ref&gt; began airing in parallel to the main program. This version, designed in a sitcom format, used re-edited scenes from the main program, as well as previously unseen footage. The intention was to further develop the plots in the comedy-drama in a sitcom style. It also focused only on Ally's personal life, cutting all the courtroom plots. The repackaged show did not catch on and was canceled partway through its initial run. While 13 episodes of ''Ally'' were created, only 10 of those 13 were actually broadcast.

