&lt;div class=&quot;references-small&quot;&gt;&lt;references group=nb/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

===One-act plays===

There are seven one-act plays written by Alan Ayckbourn. Five of them (''Mother Figure'', ''Drinking Companion'', ''Between Mouthfuls'', ''Gosforth’s Fete'' and ''A Talk in the Park'') were written for ''[[Confusions]]'', first performed in 1974.

The other two one-act plays were:
* ''Countdown'', first performed in 1962, most well-known as part of ''[[Mixed Doubles (play)|Mixed Doubles]]'', a set of short one-act plays and monologues contributed by nine different authors.
* ''A Cut in the Rates'', performed at the Stephen Joseph Theatre in 1984, and filmed for a BBC documentary.

===Books===

* {{cite book|first=Alan|last=Ayckbourn|title=The Crafty Art of Playmaking|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|location=USA|year=2003|isbn=1-4039-6229-4}}
* {{cite book|first=Alan|last=Ayckbourn|title=The Crafty Art of Playmaking|publisher= Faber and Faber|location=UK|year=2004|isbn=0-571-21510-6}}

===Film adaptations of Ayckbourn plays===

Plays adapted as films include:

* ''[[A Chorus of Disapproval (play)]]'' filmed as ''[[A Chorus of Disapproval]]'' (1988 film), directed by [[Michael Winner]];
* ''Intimate Exchanges'' (play) filmed as ''[[Smoking/No Smoking]]'' (1993 film), directed by [[Alain Resnais]];
* ''[[The Revengers' Comedies]]'' (play) filmed as ''[[Sweet Revenge (1998 film)]]'', directed by [[Malcolm Mowbray]];
* ''[[Private Fears in Public Places]]'' (play) filmed as ''[[Cœurs]]'' (2006 film) directed by [[Alain Resnais]].

