{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[642]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Maserfield]] &amp;ndash; [[Penda of Mercia]] defeats and kills [[Oswald of Northumbria]].
* [[910]] &amp;ndash; The last major [[Denmark|Danish]] army to raid [[Kingdom of England|England]] is defeated at the [[Battle of Tettenhall]] by the allied forces of [[Mercia]] and [[Wessex]], led by King [[Edward the Elder]] and [[Earl Aethelred of Mercia]].
*[[1100]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry I of England|Henry I]] is crowned [[List of English monarchs|King of England]] in [[Westminster Abbey]].
*[[1305]] &amp;ndash; [[William Wallace]], who led the [[Scotland|Scottish]] resistance against England, is captured by the English near [[Glasgow]] and transported to [[London]] where he is put on trial and executed.
*[[1388]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Otterburn]], a border skirmish between the [[Scottish people|Scottish]] and the [[English people|English]] in Northern England, is fought near [[Otterburn, Northumberland|Otterburn]].
*[[1583]] &amp;ndash; Sir [[Humphrey Gilbert]] establishes the first English [[colony]] in [[North America]], at what is now [[St John's, Newfoundland]].
*[[1600]] &amp;ndash; The [[John Ruthven, 3rd Earl of Gowrie#Gowrie conspiracy|Gowrie Conspiracy]] against [[James I of England|King James VI of Scotland]] (later to become King [[James I of England]]) takes place.
*[[1620]] &amp;ndash; The ''[[Mayflower]]'' departs from [[Southampton, England]] on its first attempt to reach [[North America]].
*[[1689]] &amp;ndash; 1,500 [[Iroquois]] attack the village of [[Lachine, Quebec|Lachine]] in [[New France]].
*[[1716]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Petrovaradin]] takes place.
*[[1735]] &amp;ndash; [[Freedom of the press]]: New York Weekly Journal writer [[John Peter Zenger]] is acquitted of [[seditious libel]] against the royal governor of [[New Yourk City|New York]], on the basis that what he had published was true.
*[[1763]] &amp;ndash; [[Pontiac's War]]: [[Battle of Bushy Run]] &amp;ndash; [[Great Britain|British]] forces led by [[Henry Bouquet]] defeat [[Chief Pontiac]]'s [[Native Americans in the United States|Indians]] at [[Bushy Run]].
*[[1772]] &amp;ndash; The [[First Partition of Poland]] begins.
*[[1781]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Dogger Bank (1781)|Battle of Dogger Bank]] takes place.
*[[1858]] &amp;ndash; [[Cyrus West Field]] and others complete the first [[transatlantic telegraph cable]] after several unsuccessful attempts. It will operate for less than a month.
*[[1860]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles XV of Sweden]] of Sweden-Norway is crowned king of [[Norway]] in [[Trondheim]].
*[[1861]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: in order to help pay for the war effort, the [[United States government]] levies the first [[income tax]] as part of the [[Revenue Act of 1861]] (3% of all incomes over US $800; rescinded in [[1872]]).
*  1861   &amp;ndash; The [[United States Army]] abolishes [[flogging]].
*[[1862]] &amp;ndash; American Civil War: [[Battle of Baton Rouge (1862)|Battle of Baton Rouge]] &amp;ndash; along the [[Mississippi River]] near [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]], [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] troops drive Union forces back into the city.
*[[1864]] &amp;ndash; American Civil War: the [[Battle of Mobile Bay]] begins &amp;ndash; at [[Mobile Bay]] near [[Mobile, Alabama]], [[Admiral]] [[David Farragut]] leads a Union flotilla through Confederate defenses and seals one of the last major Southern ports.
*[[1870]] &amp;ndash; [[Franco-Prussian War]]: the [[Battle of Spicheren]] is fought, resulting in a [[Kingdom of Prussia|Prussian]] victory.
*[[1874]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan]] launches its [[postal savings system]], modeled after a similar system in the [[United Kingdom]].
*[[1882]] &amp;ndash; The [[Standard Oil of New Jersey]] is established.
*[[1884]] &amp;ndash; The cornerstone for the [[Statue of Liberty]] is laid on [[Liberty Island|Bedloe's Island]] (now Liberty Island) in [[New York Harbor]].
*[[1888]] &amp;ndash; [[Bertha Benz]] drives from [[Mannheim]] to [[Pforzheim]] and back in the first long distance automobile trip, commemorated as the [[Bertha Benz Memorial Route]] since 2008.
*[[1901]] &amp;ndash; [[Peter O'Connor]] sets the first [[International Association of Athletics Federations|IAAF]] recognised [[long jump]] [[athletics world record|world record]] of 24&amp;nbsp;ft 11¾ins. The record will stand for 20 years.
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: the German [[minelayer]] ''[[SS Königin Luise (1913)|Königin Luise]]'' lays a minefield about 40 miles of the [[Thames Estuary]] ([[Lowestoft]]). She is intercepted and sunk by the British light-cruiser ''[[HMS Amphion (1911)|HMS Amphion]]''.
*  1914   &amp;ndash; In [[Cleveland, Ohio]], the first electric [[traffic light]] is installed.
*[[1925]] &amp;ndash; [[Plaid Cymru]] is formed with the aim of disseminating knowledge of the [[Welsh language]] that is at the time in danger of dying out.
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: the [[Soviet Union]] formally [[Soviet occupation of Latvia in 1940#1940-1941: The first Soviet occupation|annexes]] [[Latvia]].
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; World War II: possibly the biggest prison breakout in history occurs as 545 [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[POW]]s [[Cowra breakout|attempt to escape]] outside the town of [[Cowra]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]].
*  1944   &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Poland|Polish]] insurgents liberate a [[Germany|German]] [[labor camp]] in [[Warsaw]], freeing 348 [[Jews|Jewish]] prisoners.
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; In [[Ecuador]] an [[earthquake]] destroys 50 towns and kills more than 6,000.
*  1949   &amp;ndash; The [[Mann Gulch fire]] kills 13 firefighters in [[Montana]].
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; ''[[American Bandstand]]'', a show dedicated to the teenage &quot;baby-boomers&quot; by playing the songs and showing popular dances of the time, debuts on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] television network.
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Burkina Faso]], then known as [[Republic of Upper Volta|Upper Volta]], becomes independent from [[French Fourth Republic|France]].
*[[1962]] &amp;ndash; [[Nelson Mandela]] is jailed. He would not be released until [[1990]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States]], the [[United Kingdom]], and the [[Soviet Union]] sign a [[Treaty Banning Nuclear Weapon Tests in the Atmosphere, in Outer Space, and Under Water|nuclear test ban treaty]].
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Operation Pierce Arrow]] &amp;ndash; [[United States|American]] aircraft from carriers {{USS|Ticonderoga|CV-14|6}} and {{USS|Constellation|CV-64|6}} bomb [[North Vietnam]] in retaliation for strikes against U.S. destroyers in the [[Gulf of Tonkin]].
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; [[Mariner program]]: ''[[Mariner 7]]'' makes its closest fly-by of [[Mars]] (3,524 kilometers).
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: the [[Congress of the United States|U.S. Congress]] places a $1 billion dollar limit on military aid to [[South Vietnam]].
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; In [[Afghanistan]], [[Afghanistan Liberation Organization|Maoists]] undertake an attempted military uprising.
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Ronald Reagan]] [[Professional Air Traffic Controllers Organization (1968)|fires]] 11,359 [[Strike action|striking]] air-traffic controllers who ignored his order for them to return to work.
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; General elections are held in [[Nicaragua]] with the [[Sandinista Front]] winning a majority.
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; The city of [[Knin]], a significant [[Serb]] stronghold, is captured by [[Croatia]]n forces during [[Operation Storm]]. The date is celebrated in Croatia as [[Victory Day (Croatia)|Victory Day]].
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; A [[2003 Marriott Hotel bombing|car bomb]] explodes in the [[Indonesia]]n capital of [[Jakarta]] outside the [[Marriott Hotel]] killing 12 and injuring 150.
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[2010 Copiapó mining accident]] occurs, trapping 33 Chilean miners approximately 2,300&amp;nbsp;ft below the ground.

